    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>CONSTRUCTION BILL SIGNED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Debra Nussbaum</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Nussbaum, Debra</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Gov Christine Whitman signs 5-year, $8.6 billion school construction and renovation bill, $6 billion of which will go to 30 financially disadvantaged urban districts (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Governor Whitman last week signed a bill that will provide $8.6 billion for school construction or renovation over the next five years. Of the money, $6 billion will go to  30 financially disadvantaged urban districts and $2.6 billion to other districts. The bill comes two years after the state  supreme court ordered the state to improve buildings in the poorest districts.</p>
        <p>Debra Nussbaum</p>
      </block>
